"tt\"/> It was released by [[Viking Press]] in 2019. \n\n==Summary==\n''10 Minutes and 38 Seconds in This Strange World'' opens in 1990 with \u201cTequila Leila\u201d, who is a prostitute.<ref name=\"tg1\"/> <ref>[http://www.ourdailyread.com/2019/06/10-minutes-38-seconds-in-this-strange-world-by-elif-shafak-review-powerful-but-preachy/ \u201c10 Minutes 38 Seconds in This Strange World by Elif Shafak review \u2013 powerful but preachy\u201d], \u201cOur Daily Read\u201d, June 16, 2019,</ref>  The story has her five outcast friends, who don\u2019t share a worthy importance in a liberal country.<ref name=\"tg1\"/> Leila enters the state of awareness in her last moments after she has been murdered and left in a dumpster outside Istanbul. <ref name=\"ban\"/> \u201cWhile the Turkish sun rises above her and her friends asleep soundly nearby, she contemplates her mortal existence before eternal rest.\u201d<ref name=\"ban\"/> In the last minutes she recalls her previous life; \u201cthe taste of spiced goat stew, sacrificed by her father to celebrate the long-awaited birth of a son; the sight of bubbling vats of lemon and sugar which the women use to wax their legs while the men attend mosque; the scent of cardamom coffee that Leila shares with a handsome student in the brothel where she works. Each memory, too, recalls the friends she made at each key moment in her life \u2013 friends who are now desperately trying to find her. . .\u201d <ref>[https://www.curtisbrown.co.uk/client/elif-shafak-1/work/10-minutes-38-seconds-in-this-strange-world \u201c10 Minutes 38 Seconds in This Strange World\u201d], \u201cCurtis Brown\u201d,</ref><ref>[https://www.penguin.co.uk/books/303/303783/10-minutes-38-seconds-in-this-strange-world/9780241293867.html \u201c10 Minutes 38 Seconds in This Strange World Elif Shafak\u201d], \u201cPenguin\u201d,</ref> <ref>[https://www.easons.com/10-minutes-38-seconds-in-this-strange-world-elif-shafak-9780241293867 \u201c10 MINUTES 38 SECONDS IN THIS STRANGE WORLD\u201d],\u201deasons\u201d,June  06, 2019</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n\u2022\tShortlisted for the [[Booker Prize]] 2019.<ref>[https://thebookerprizes.com/fiction \u201cThe Booker Prize - The Shortlist\u201d], \u201cThe Booker Prizes\u201d, 2019</ref><ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/books/booker-prize-2019-the-books-to-read-and-the-ones-you-can-skip-1.4037691 \"Booker Prize 2019: The books to read, and the ones you can skip\"],\"The Irish Times\",October 12, 2019</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/books/2019/oct/13/man-booker-prize-2019-shortlist \"Booker prize shortlist 2019: who to put your money on\"],\"The Guardian\",October 13, 2019</ref><ref>[https://www.thestatesman.com/world/booker-prize-2019-atwood-rushdie-and-four-emerging-authors-up-for-prize-1502809684.html \"Booker Prize 2019: Atwood, Rushdie and four emerging authors up for prize\"],\"The Statesman\",October 14, 2019</ref>\n\n\u2022\tThe Blackwell\u2019s Book of the Year, 2019<ref>https://blackwells.co.uk/bookshop/product/10-Minutes-38-Seconds-in-This-Strange-World-by-Elif-Shafak-author/9780241293867?fbclid=IwAR0pcVazDujniPAIPV6RM6JONRnpkFM8UC5AIjJhloHRUrH-eHsqWS1EPvE</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"ban\">[https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/10-minutes-38-seconds-in-this-strange-world-elif-shafak/1132393876#/ \u201c10 Minutes 38 Seconds in This Strange World\u201d], \u201cBarnes & Noble\u201d,</ref>\n<ref name=\"tg1\">[https://www.theguardian.com/books/2019/jun/16/10-minutes-38-seconds-in-this-strange-world-by-elif-shafak-book-review \u201c10 Minutes 38 Seconds in This Strange World by Elif Shafak review \u2013 powerful but preachy\u201d], \u201cThe Guardian\u201d, June 16, 2019,</ref>\n<ref name=\"tt\">[https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/10-minutes-38-seconds-in-this-strange-world-by-elif-shafak-review-gnqjrn5nd \u201c10 Minutes 38 Seconds in This Strange World by Elif Shafak review \u2014 memories of a prostitute\u201d], \u201cThe Times\u201d, June 07, 2019,</ref>\n}}\